        <briefdescription>
<para>Computes the in-place Radix-2 Decimation-in-Time FFT. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>n must be a power of 2 (e.g., 8, 16, 32, 64, 128, 256). Max supported size is 256.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>real</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Array of real parts (size n). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>imag</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Array of imaginary parts (size n). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>n</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Size of the FFT (must be power of 2). </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para>SYN_OK on success, SYN_ERROR on invalid parameters (e.g. not power of 2). </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
